d by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes de Malpas had at least 1 son with Nigel le Puis."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1100–Male":"1100–Surnud","1090–1134":"1090–1134","–Female":"Surnud","1090":"1090","about 1090":"umbes 1090","1134":"1134","1100":"1100","Malpas, Cheshire, England":"Malpas, Cheshire, England"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1100–Male":"1100–Kuollut","1090–1134":"1090–1134","–Female":"Kuollut","1090":"1090","about 1090":"noin 1090","1134":"1134","1100":"1100","Malpas, Cheshire, England":"Malpas, Cheshire, England"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","1100–Male":"1100–Décédé","1090–1134":"1090–1134","–Female":"Décédée","1090":"1090","about 1090":"environ 1090","1134":"1134","1100":"1100","Malpas, Cheshire, England":"Malpas, Cheshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Agnes de Malpas a eu au moins 1 fils avec Nigel le Puis."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","1100–Male":"1100–Verstorben","1090–1134":"1090–1134","–Female":"Verstorben","1090":"1090","about 1090":"um 1090","1134":"1134","1100":"1100","Malpas, Cheshire, England":"Malpas, Cheshire, England","lifeSummary":"Agnes de Malpas hatte mit Nigel le Puis mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"–":"Desede","1100–Male":"1100–Desede","1090–1134":"1090–1134","–Female":"Desede","1090":"1090","about 1090":"about 1090","1134":"1134","1100":"1100","Malpas, Cheshire, England":"Malpas, Cheshire, England"},"hu":{"–":"elhunyt","1100–Male":"1100–elhunyt","1090–1134":"1090–1134","–Female":"elhunyt","1090":"1090","about 1090":"1090 körül","1134":"1134","1100":"1100","Malpas, Cheshire, England":"Malpas, Cheshire, England"},"id":{"–":"Telah Meninggal","1100–Male":"1100–Telah Meninggal","1090–1134":"1090–1134","–Female":"Telah Meninggal","1090":"1090","about 1090":"sekitar 1090","1134":"1134","1100":"1100","Malpas, Cheshire, England":"M